SIMPLE: fondling
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fondling
<hw>Fon"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Fondle</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of caressing; manifestation of
tenderness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cyrus made no . . . amorous <qex>fondling</qex>⟦br⟧
To fan her pride, or melt her guardless heart.</q>
<rj><qau>Mickle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fondling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fondling
<hw>Fond"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Fond</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person or thing fondled or
caressed; one treated with foolish or doting affection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Fondlings</qex> are in danger to be made fools.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fool; a simpleton; a ninny.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fondly</ent>⟦br⟧
